<article><span id="spanTopic" class="topicLabel">[Connecting the Dots](/articles#!topic:connecting-the-dots) </span><span id="spanType" class="articleType">[Pop Explains](/articles#!articletype:pop-explains) </span><span id="hArticleDescription" style="display: none">Most of us have heard of the (in)famous population projection of 6.9M by 2030, but what is this number used for, and what does it say about our future</span>

### Do we need a population projection?

<span id="spanAuthor" class="articleAuthor"></span><span id="spanPubDate" class="articleDate">2 Aug, 2016</span>

<footer><span class="popsgicon popsgicon-facebook share hide"></span><span class="facebook-share-count"></span><span class="popsgicon popsgicon-twitter share hide"></span><span class="hide" data-bind="text: mediaShares.twitter()"></span><span class="popsgicon popsgicon-email share hide"></span><span class="hide" data-bind="text: mediaShares.email()"></span><span class="popsgicon popsgicon-text-resize hidden-lg"></span><span class="hidden-lg">Text size</span></footer>

